01778 is a 5-digit zip code located in Wayland, Massachusetts. Wayland is the primary city for 01778 and is located in Portage. In the most recent US census the population of 01778 was 14132.

There are a total of 5,346 housing units in 01778, Massachusetts. A total of 3.39% (181) are currently vacant.

Total Population by Age

01778 has a total population of 14,132. In the bar chart and table below, this population is split into 18 different age range segments.

Most inhabitants of 01778 are in the 55 to 59 years age bracket. As of the last census, there are 1,341 people in this segment.

The 85 years and over segment is the smallest age range in 01778. There are just 343 people in this category.

Race and Gender Population of 01778

Women make up the highest portion of people in 01778. There are 6,937 men and 7,133 women in this 5-digit zip code.

There are no people who identify as: American Indian in this 01778 zip code.

Most people in this zip code are White, with a total of 11,305 people in this category.

Bedrooms, Rooms and Units in Structures in 01778

Below are three pie charts and tables showing the amount of bedrooms, total rooms and structures in houses for this zip code.

Most houses in 01778 have 5 or more bedrooms, with a total of 27 houses.

In regards to rooms in general, people in this zip code have an average of 7.7 rooms in their house. Most houses actually have 9 rooms or more in their house. 1,858 homes fit into this category.

1,858 homes in 01778 are in the 1-unit, detached category, which is the most common in terms of structures for this area.
